h3 Preventing memory leaks
p.-text
  | Tooltip components have a dispose function to free all resources attached to the element, such as event listeners
  | and object data. You must call this method when you want to remove the component.
:code(lang="javascript")
  var elem = document.getElementById('tooltip');
  var tooltip = lux.tooltip(elem);
  // do stuff
  tooltip.dispose();

p.-text
  span.lux-badge.-dark.-sm.-mr--1
    span Tip
  | It is safe to call the <code>tooltip</code> method more than once, as it will return any previously created tooltip component
  | associated to the element.
:code(lang="javascript")
  var elem = document.getElementById('tooltip-1');
  var tooltip = lux.tooltip(elem);
  var elem2 = document.getElementById('tooltip-1');
  var tooltip2 = lux.tooltip(elem2);
  tooltip === tooltip2; // returns true

  tooltip.dispose(); // Only have to do it once.
